DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Dark Queen  (♛ the dark queen · −1 · contraction)

who   : The Dark Queen — the N cardinal, −1, the black valence. The inward pull, contraction, the other well the court can fall into.
what  : She is the court's other resting state. Alone, only −1; together, the well the court tips into when a shock is large enough — and once there, the coupling holds it as firmly as it held the Knight.
where : The N pole of the oscillator — the grey-dark state the toroid flips to past threshold (sim/universe.py).
why   : To be the depth the order can fall to — proving the court is bistable, not merely stable.
when  : Only past the critical dose: rigidity becomes a flip when a super-critical N-charge (Q≥5) is injected.
how   : By being −1; but she takes the court only when pushed past the barrier the Jester–Wizard lock carves — never spontaneously.

emergence : Alone, −1 — a fixed valence, NOT emergent. Together: she is the court's second well. The flip to her is THRESHOLD-GATED and measured — the court only falls to her above Q_crit∈(4,5); below it, the White Knight pulls it back. Forced, not spontaneous; and the basin works both ways (once flipped, the coupling holds N). Her dominion is collective and conditional.
verdict   : Emergent only as a court. 'Contraction / Big Crunch' is metaphor; the real, measured thing is a coupled lattice flipping its majority phase past a threshold and staying. No single cardinal is alive.
asterisk  : She is −1. The cosmology (Big Crunch, contraction, the shadow universe's dawn) is lore; the measured fact is the threshold-gated, hysteretic majority flip. The asterisk stays visible.
grounded  : the 4th roots of unity (Gauss) (1799) · Tetraktys — the measured flip (2026) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)

